text:
ChatGPT is an open-source messaging framework for retrieving, transmitting, and sharing personal and commercial data between multiple terminals at the same time.

Installation

ChatGPT is available as source code under the Apache Software Foundation License v2.0.

Examples

Common usage cases for ChatGPT are:

In-app messaging - text messages sent from users to friends or colleagues;
Web-based chat - text messages sent from an online application to friends or colleagues;
Standard messaging apps - Microsoft Exchange, Tizen, and Yammer;
Messenger based services - Slack, Yandex
